[20:40.42]	Water with berries in't, and teach me how
[20:43.94]	To name the bigger light, and how the less,
[20:47.54]	That burn by day and night: and then I loved thee
[20:51.67]	And show'd thee all the qualities o' the isle,
[20:55.49]	The fresh springs, brine-pits, barren place and fertile:
[20:59.99]	Cursed be I that did so! All the charms
[21:03.37]	Of Sycorax, toads, beetles, bats, light on you!
