[21:40.41]	Thou didst prevent me; I had peopled else
[21:43.94]	This isle with Calibans.
[21:46.19]PROSPERO	Abhorred slave,
[21:47.76]	Which any print of goodness wilt not take,
[21:51.36]	Being capable of all ill! I pitied thee,
[21:54.74]	Took pains to make thee speak, taught thee each hour
[21:59.09]	One thing or other: when thou didst not, savage,
[22:02.98]	Know thine own meaning, but wouldst gabble like
[22:06.96]	A thing most brutish, I endow'd thy purposes
[22:10.71]	With words that made them known. But thy vile race,
[22:14.91]	Though thou didst learn, had that in't which
[22:18.66]	good natures
[22:20.08]	Could not abide to be with; therefore wast thou
[22:24.06]	Deservedly confined into this rock,
[22:27.13]	Who hadst deserved more than a prison.
